cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.DB, cs.NE

This paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category as it deals with the MapReduce computation framework for processing large amounts of data in both public and private clouds. It could also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category as it involves choosing suitable values for MapReduce configuration parameters and predicting the amount of resources required. Additionally, it could be classified under Software Engineering (cs.SE) as it presents an approach to provision the total CPU usage in clock cycles of jobs in MapReduce environment. It could also be categorized under Databases (cs.DB) as it deals with data mining tasks, and Networked and Online Social Networks (cs.NE) as it involves spam detection.
